libbc-runtime (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * feat(error_collector): add `bc_runtime_error_collector_*` public API.
    Thread-safe (atomic_flag-protected append), inlined 512-byte path
    buffer per record, optional `stage` field. Replaces the three
    separate collector implementations previously duplicated in
    bc-seek, bc-hash and bc-duplicate (~300 LOC eliminated across
    consumers).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Tue, 21 Apr 2026 21:40:00 +0000

libbc-runtime (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release.
  * Application lifecycle: bc_runtime_app_* init/run/cleanup flow.
  * CLI framework: argv parsing, subcommand dispatch, help rendering.
  * Layered configuration with typed accessors and env overrides.
  * Structured log sink with level filtering.
  * Metrics: counter / gauge / histogram primitives.
  * Full sanitizer coverage (asan / tsan / ubsan / memcheck) and
    cppcheck-clean sources.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Sun, 19 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0000
